Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.499 --> 00:00:03.120
What would make someone want to
move from California to become

00:00:03.120 --> 00:00:05.040
a middle school teacher
in one of the poorest

00:00:05.040 --> 00:00:06.930
areas of Baltimore, Maryland?

00:00:06.930 --> 00:00:07.785
Take a look.

00:00:07.785 --> 00:00:09.270
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:09.270 --> 00:00:11.310
Go over to your worksheet now.

00:00:11.310 --> 00:00:13.961
Can you read that question up
at the top nice and loud for us?

00:00:13.961 --> 00:00:14.460
Hi.

00:00:14.460 --> 00:00:16.615
My name is Wyatt Oroke,
but my kids call me Mr. O.

00:00:16.615 --> 00:00:18.990
And I'm the humanities teacher
at City Springs Elementary

00:00:18.990 --> 00:00:21.560
Middle School in Baltimore.

00:00:21.560 --> 00:00:23.340
There are neighborhoods
within Baltimore

00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:25.290
that have been under-resourced
and underserved

00:00:25.290 --> 00:00:28.210
for centuries based on
political decisions made,

00:00:28.210 --> 00:00:30.930
be it segregated
housing or redlining

00:00:30.930 --> 00:00:32.100
certain neighborhoods.

00:00:32.100 --> 00:00:34.830
And so what that has led
to is that our students

00:00:34.830 --> 00:00:37.140
come from the highest poverty
rates out of any school

00:00:37.140 --> 00:00:39.040
in Baltimore City.

00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:40.800
Since I've been
teaching, I've had

00:00:40.800 --> 00:00:42.990
students who have been
homeless every single year.

00:00:42.990 --> 00:00:45.217
I lost a student
to gun violence.

00:00:45.217 --> 00:00:47.300
I've had a couple students
give birth to children.

00:00:47.300 --> 00:00:50.140
One of them went into
labor in my classroom.

00:00:50.140 --> 00:00:52.680
And so for me, it's trying
to show as much empathy

00:00:52.680 --> 00:00:54.570
as I can, and just
be a listening ear.

00:00:54.570 --> 00:00:56.220
A lot of times, what
our students like

00:00:56.220 --> 00:00:57.737
is just someone to hear them.

00:00:57.737 --> 00:00:59.050
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:59.050 --> 00:01:01.770
Growing up in Baltimore
has been very challenging.

00:01:01.770 --> 00:01:04.855
It just made me strong
and independent.

00:01:04.855 --> 00:01:07.170
And my mother always told
me to be independent.

00:01:07.170 --> 00:01:10.110
